# n8n AI Agent Rules

Read `f:\Prime\n8n\MASTER_KNOWLEDGE.md` §4 (AI Agent Architecture) before building any AI agent workflow. Also read `f:\Prime\.cursor\skills\n8n-ai-agent-builder\SKILL.md`.

---

## AI Agent Architecture (§4)

```
[Trigger: Webhook / Chat / Schedule]
        │
        ▼
[@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent]   ← MAIN AGENT NODE
        │
        ├── ai_languageModel → [lmOpenAi / lmChatAnthropic / lmChatGoogleGemini]
        ├── ai_tool          → [toolHttpRequest / toolCode / toolPostgres / ...]
        ├── ai_tool          → [Multiple tools supported]
        ├── ai_memory        → [memoryWindowBuffer / memoryPostgresChatMemory]
        └── ai_outputParser  → [structuredOutputParser — optional]
        │
        ▼
[n8n-nodes-base.webhookResponse / Slack / Email / DB]
```

---

## AI Connection Types (§4)

| Connection Type | What connects to the agent | Direction |
|----------------|--------------------------|-----------|
| `ai_languageModel` | LLM model node | model → agent |
| `ai_tool` | Tool nodes (HTTP, DB, Code) | tool → agent |
| `ai_memory` | Memory node | memory → agent |
| `ai_outputParser` | Output parser node | parser → agent |

---

## LangChain Node Prefixes (§2)

**ALL LangChain nodes use `@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.*` — NOT `n8n-nodes-base.*`**

```
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent              ← Main agent
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmOpenAi           ← OpenAI GPT-4
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatAnthropic    ← Claude
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGoogleGemini ← Gemini
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.memoryWindowBuffer ← Conversation memory
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.memoryPostgresChatMemory ← Persistent memory
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolHttpRequest    ← HTTP tool
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolCode          ← Code execution tool
```

---

## Build Steps for AI Agent Workflows

```
1. n8n_create_workflow({name: "AI Agent", nodes: [trigger, agent], connections: {...}})
2. n8n_update_partial_workflow({intent: "attach OpenAI model",
     operations: [{type: "addNode", node: {type: "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmOpenAi"}}]})
3. n8n_update_partial_workflow({intent: "connect model to agent",
     operations: [{type: "addConnection", source: "OpenAI", target: "AI Agent",
                   connectionType: "ai_languageModel"}]})
4. Attach memory via ai_memory connection
5. Attach tools via ai_tool connections (one operation per tool)
6. n8n_validate_workflow({id}) — use profile: "ai-friendly" for agent workflows
7. activateWorkflow
```

---

## Validation for AI Agents (§5)

Use `profile: "ai-friendly"` (not `runtime`) — reduces false positives common in AI workflow configurations.

```javascript
validate_node({
  nodeType: "nodes-base.agent",
  config: {...},
  profile: "ai-friendly"   // ← Use this for AI agent nodes
})
```

---

## Common AI Agent Mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Using `n8n-nodes-base.agent` | Use `@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent` |
| Connecting model with wrong connection type | Use `ai_languageModel` (not `main`) |
| No memory = no multi-turn conversation | Always attach memoryWindowBuffer for chat use cases |
| `strict` validation on AI workflows | Use `ai-friendly` — AI nodes have looser config requirements |
| One-shot workflow creation | Build iteratively: agent → model → memory → tools |
